parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine overheating at low speeds can cause the motorcycle to stall or seize, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially in congested traffic conditions.
symptoms: The engine overheats at speeds below 15-20 mph
the temperature gauge enters the red zone
the coolant overflow tank vents coolant onto the rear tire
the radiator fans blow forward into the direction of travel
the engine requires high speeds to cool down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate speedometer readings can cause safety problems, particularly on high-speed roads, as drivers may be unaware of their actual speed, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Speedometer readings are consistently 6-8% higher than actual speed
odometer readings are consistently 6% higher than actual distance traveled
drivers must constantly calculate their actual speed
leading to distraction and increased risk of accidents.
